Add / edit attribute value While adding or editing an attribute value, the following fields / toggles / parameters are displayed:
 Attribute group  This drop-down lists all the attributes and is mandatory. In the case of multistore, it lists only the attributes associated with the store(s) selected as context. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Choose the attribute group for this value.&rdquo;
Value  This field is mandatory and can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty for the default language, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The field value is required at least in default language&rdquo; When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Invalid characters: &lt;&gt;;=#{}&rdquo;.
URL  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed URLs by choosing the word that best represents this attribute. By default, PrestaShop uses the attribute&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo; When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Invalid characters: &lt;&gt;;=#{}_&rdquo;.
Meta title  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed page titles by choosing the word that best represents this attribute. By default, PrestaShop uses the attribute&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo;
Shop association  The shop association block is displayed when the multistore is enabled and if several shops are configured.
👉 See the specs of the shop association block
Color  This color picker is displayed only if the selected attribute is of type color or texture. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Choose a color with the color picker, or enter an HTML color (e.g. &ldquo;lightblue&rdquo;, &ldquo;#CC6600&quot;&rdquo;. The color can be filled in the input or selected with the color picker. If the color filled in the field is incorrect, while clicking on save, an error message is displayed: &ldquo;The color field is invalid.&rdquo;
Texture  This field is displayed only if the selected attribute is of type color or texture. It allows uploading a texture/picture. When clicking on the &ldquo;Add file&rdquo; button, a pop-up is opened and allows to choose a file to upload. Only the following formats are allowed to be uploaded: .gif, .jpg, .png. If a texture is uploaded and if the color is filled, the texture is used and not the color. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Upload an image file containing the color texture from your computer. This will override the HTML color.&rdquo;. When trying to upload an incorrect format file and trying to save, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;Image format not recognized, allowed formats are: .gif, .jpg, .png&rdquo;
Current texture  When there is no texture, a message &ldquo;None&rdquo; is displayed. When there is a texture, the texture is displayed with a &ldquo;delete&rdquo; button. If pressing &ldquo;delete&rdquo;, the texture is deleted and the following message is displayed: &ldquo;The image was successfully deleted.&rdquo;
Call to action 3 call to actions are displayed at the bottom of this page:
  Save then add another value: In the case of adding an attribute value, the attribute value is added and the add form is opened and a success message is displayed: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing an attribute value, the attribute value is edited and the add form is opened and a success message is displayed: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;
  Save: In the case of adding an attribute value, the attribute value is added and a success message is displayed on the attribute values listing: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing an attribute value, the attribute value is edited and a success message is displayed on the attribute values listing: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;.
  Cancel: The attribute value is not added/edited and the attribute values listing is displayed.

Add / Edit Feature While adding or editing a feature, the following fields / toggles / parameters are displayed:
 Name  This field is mandatory. If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty for the default language, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The field name is required at least in default language&rdquo;. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down.
URL  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed URLs by choosing the word that best represent this feature. By default, PrestaShop uses the feature&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo;
Meta title  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed page titles by choosing the word that best represent this feature. By default, PrestaShop uses the feature&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo;
Indexable  This toggle is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows to enable or disable the use of the generated URL for faceted search. By default, this toggle is enabled. There is a help-text under the toggle: &ldquo;Use this attribute in URL generated by the Faceted Search module.&rdquo;
Shop association  The shop association block is displayed when the multistore is enabled and if several shops are configured.
👉 See the specs of the shop association block
Call to action There are 2 buttons at the bottom of this page:
 Cancel: The feature is not added/edited and the listing is displayed Save: In the case of adding a feature, the feature is added and a success message is displayed on the listing: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing a feature, the feature is edited and a success message is displayed on the listing: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;.

Add / Edit Feature Value While adding or editing a feature value, the following fields / toggles / parameters are displayed:
 Feature  This drop-down lists all the features and is mandatory. In the case of multistore, it lists only the features associated with the store(s) selected as context.
Value  This field is mandatory and can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty for the default language, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The field value is required at least in default language&rdquo;
URL  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed URLs by choosing the word that best represent this feature. By default, PrestaShop uses the feature&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo;
Meta title  This field is displayed only when the facetedsearch module is enabled. It allows searching for the value more precisely. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. There is a help-text under this field: &ldquo;When the Faceted Search module is enabled, you can get more detailed page titles by choosing the word that best represent this feature. By default, PrestaShop uses the feature&rsquo;s name, but you can change that setting using this field.&rdquo;
Call to action There are 3 buttons at the bottom of this page:
 Cancel: The feature value is not added/edited and the feature values listing is displayed. Save then add another value: In the case of adding a feature value, the feature value is added and the add form is opened and a success message is displayed: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing a feature value, the feature value is edited and the add form is opened and a success message is displayed: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo; Save: In the case of adding a feature value, the feature value is added and a success message is displayed on the feature values listing: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing a feature value, the feature value is edited and a success message is displayed on the feature values listing: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;.

Add / Edit Store While adding or editing a store, the following fields/toggles/drop downs/parameters are displayed:
 Name  This input field allows to fill the name of the store. It can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed &ldquo;Store name (e.g. City Center Mall Store). Allowed characters: letters, spaces and %s&rdquo;
Address  This input field allows to fill the address of the store. This field is mandatory and can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down. If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The field address1 is required at least in default language&rdquo;
Address (2)  This input field allows to fill the second address line of the store. This field can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down.
Zip/Postal code  This input field allows to fill the zip/postal code of the store. The field is mandatory, if the field is empty when trying to save, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;A Zip/Postal code is required.&rdquo;. If the postal code exceeds 12 characters when trying to save, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The postcode field is too long (12 chars max).&rdquo;. If the format isn&rsquo;t correct when saving, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The Zip/Postal code is invalid. It must be entered as follows: 00000&rdquo;. The format of the postal code is defined for each country in International &gt; Locations &gt; Countries &gt; Add/edit country.
City  This input field allows to fill the city of the store and is mandatory. If more than 64 chars are filled the following message is dislayed: &ldquo;The city field is too long (64 chars max).&rdquo; If invalid chars are filled the following message is displayed: &ldquo;The city field is invalid.&rdquo; If the save button is pressed and if this field is empty, the following error message is displayed &ldquo;The city field is required.&rdquo;
Country  This drop-down allows to select the country of the store and is mandatory. While creating a new store, the default country (selected in International &gt; Localization &gt; Configuration) is selected by default.
State (displayed only for the countries that have states, as defined in International &gt; Locations &gt; States.)  This drop-down allows to select the state of the store and is mandatory. If no state is selected when trying to save, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;An address located in a country containing states must have a state selected.&rdquo;
Latitude/Longtitude  There are 2 separate input fields for the latitude and longitude of the store, they are both mandatory. Only numbers are allowed for these fields. When trying to input a character that is not a number, an error message is displayed: &ldquo;Latitude and longitude are required.&rdquo; The numbers in the fields are limited to 13, if there are more numbers than allowed, an error message is displayed: &ldquo;The latitude field is too long (13 chars max).&rdquo; and/or &ldquo;The longitude field is too long (13 chars max).&rdquo; When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Store coordinates (e.g. 45.265469/-47.226478).
Phone  This input field allows to fill the phone number of the store. If more than 16 chars are filled the following message is dislayed: &ldquo;The phone field is too long (16 chars max).&rdquo; Only numbers are allowed for these fields. When trying to input a character that is not a number, an error message is displayed: &ldquo;The phone field is invalid.&rdquo;
Fax  This input field allows to fill the fax number of the store. If more than 16 chars are filled the following message is dislayed: &ldquo;The phone field is too long (16 chars max).&rdquo; Only numbers are allowed for these fields. When trying to input a character that is not a number, an error message is displayed: &ldquo;The fax field is invalid.&rdquo;
Email address  This input field allows to fill the email address of the store.
Note  This input field allows to fill a note for the store. It can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the field is displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down.
Active  This toggle can be on &ldquo;yes&rdquo; or &ldquo;no&rdquo; and allows to choose if the store is active or not. By default, while creating a new store, this toggle is on &ldquo;yes&rdquo;. If the toggle is set to &ldquo;no&rdquo;, the &ldquo;Stores&rdquo; page of the front office will not be displayed or accessible. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Whether or not to display this store&rdquo;.
Picture  This field allows to upload a picture for the store. While editing a store with an existing picture, the size of the picture is displayed under the field. When the label is hovered, a tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Storefront picture.&rdquo; When trying to upload an incorrect format file, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;Image format not recognized, allowed formats are: gif, jpg, jpeg, jpe, png, webp&rdquo;
Shop association  The shop association block is displayed when the multistore is enabled and if several shops are configured.
👉 See the specs of the shop association block
Hours  Firstly an example is displayed: &ldquo;e.g. 10:00AM - 9:30PM&rdquo; For each day of the week, there is an input field allowing to fill the working hours. These fields can be translated: When several languages are installed, a drop-down next to the field is displayed. It allows choosing in which language the fields are displayed and customizing it according to the language. Disabled languages are displayed in the drop-down.
 Monday Tuesday Wednesday Thursday Friday Saturday Sunday  Call to action  Save: In the case of adding a new store, the store is added and a success message is displayed on the stores listing: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing a store, the store is edited and a success message is displayed on the stores listing: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;. Cancel: The store is not added/edited and the stores listing is displayed.

Add edit state While adding or editing a state, the following fields / drop-down / toggle are displayed:
 Name - this field is mandatory. A tooltip for this field is displayed: &ldquo;Provide the state name to be displayed in addresses and on invoices.&rdquo;. When trying to save and if the field is empty, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The name field is required.&rdquo;. When trying to save and if the field is invalid, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The name field is invalid.&rdquo;. ISO code - this field is mandatory. A tooltip for this field is displayed: &ldquo;1 to 4 letter ISO code. You can prefix it with the country ISO code if needed.&rdquo;. When trying to save and if the field is empty, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The iso_code field is required.&rdquo; When trying to save and if the field exceeds 4 characters or contains invalid characters, the following error message is displayed: &ldquo;The iso_code field is invalid.&rdquo;. Country - this drop-down is mandatory. A tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Country where the state is located. Only the countries with the option &ldquo;contains state&rdquo; enabled are displayed. Zone - this drop-down is mandatory. A tooltip is displayed: &ldquo;Geographical region where this state is located. Used for shipping&rdquo;. Status - this toggle is mandatory. It can be turned to &ldquo;yes&rdquo; or &ldquo;no&rdquo;. By default it is set to: &ldquo;yes&rdquo;.  Call to action There are 2 buttons at the bottom of this page:
 Cancel: redirects to the previous page, cancels any changes. Save: In the case of adding a state, the state is added and a success message is displayed on the listing: &ldquo;Successful creation.&rdquo;. In the case of editing a state, the state is edited and a success message is displayed on the listing: &ldquo;Successful update.&rdquo;.  Multistore This page doesn’t have a shop association block. So, the state is added/edited for all shops, no matter the context selected. The following information message is displayed at the top of this page: &ldquo;Note that this feature is available in all shops context only. It will be added to all your stores.&rdquo;

Add edit zone The following fields/toggles are displayed:
  Name: this field is mandatory. When trying to save and if the field is empty, the following error message appears: &ldquo;Please fillout this field&rdquo;. If more than 64 chars are filled the following error message appears &ldquo;This field cannot be longer than 64 characters.&rdquo;. When trying to save and if the field is invalid, the following error message is displayed &quot; &ldquo;the entered name&rdquo; is invalid.&quot; A help text is displayed: &ldquo;Zone name (e.g. Africa, West Coast, Neighboring Countries).&rdquo;
  Active This toggle can be enabled or disabled. By default, it is enabled. A help text is displayed: &ldquo;Allow or disallow shipping to this zone.&rdquo;
  Call to action  Save: In the case of adding a new zone and if there is no error, the zone is added and a success message is displayed on zones listing : &ldquo;Creation successful&rdquo;. In the case of editing a zone, the zone is edited and a success message is displayed on zones listing : &ldquo;Successful update&rdquo;. Cancel: The zone is not added/edited and zones listing is displayed.  Multistore The shop association block is displayed when the multistore is enabled and if several shops are configured.
👉 See the specs of the shop association block
